{
  "texts": [
    "The idea is to build trust through protocols and operate the system without authority (i.e., a trusted third party).",
    "A smart contract is essentially a computer-coded contract on blockchain that is automatically executed when the contract terms are met.",
    "This increases the enforceability of business contracts without the involvement of a trusted third party (Cong and He 2019).",
    "Stablecoins are cryptocurrencies designed to be price-stable by pegging their values to a specific asset (or a basket of assets), making them a better medium of exchange than typical cryptocurrencies.",
    "The most common peg is to the US dollar."
  ]
}